The '''Mobile Electronics Rocket-6A''' or '''MER-6A,''' '''Emergency Rocket Communications System''' ('''ERCS''') provided a reliable and survivable emergency communications method for the [[United States]] [[National Command Authority]], using a [[ultra high frequency|UHF]] repeater placed atop a [[Scout (rocket family)|Blue Scout]] rocket.

==Operations==
The [[Scout (rocket family)|Blue Scout]] version of ERCS (Program 279) was deployed to three sites near [[Wisner, Nebraska|Wisner]], [[West Point, Nebraska|West Point]], and [[Tekamah, Nebraska|Tekamah]], Nebraska.

